<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>ORATT:  You're mistaken. I have every right.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You can't dismiss someone just because you don't agree with the way they conduct their personal lives.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>ORATT:  I am not dismissing T'Pol. I'm simply returning her to Vulcan. The High Command will decide whether she is fit for duty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Fit? You're saying a single mind-meld is enough to destroy her career? Or is it that she contracted the disease? That's why you're so hesitant to find a cure, isn't it? Why bother to help people you don't approve of?</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>ORATT:  I'm sorry you don't understand the complexities of our culture, Captain. Please have the Sub-Commander ready to depart in thirty six hours.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Not so fast. You know what this is, Doctor? My Communications Officer got it from the Vulcan database. It's the protocols of the Council of Physicians. It says that anyone accused of ethical misconduct is entitled to a hearing before the ranking medical officer in the province or territory where the accusation was first made. If I'm not mistaken, that would be you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>ORATT:  The accusation against T'Pol stands. It's not open for debate.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Where I come from, everything's open for debate. And if I read these protocols correctly, so is the accusation you made against my Science Officer.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>ORATT:  You're wasting your time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>ARCHER:  It's mine to waste.</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>ORATT:  Very well. But I will not delay our departure. The hearing will take place tomorrow afternoon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Tomorrow afternoon. Fine.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Travis displays a magnificent bruise on his ribs.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>TRAVIS:  It's the Dekendi's favourite sport.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>PHLOX:  Just because they asked you to participate, doesn't mean you had to.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>TRAVIS:  They said it was an honour. It looked easy enough.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>PHLOX:  You're lucky this creature didn't strike a bit lower. If I may ask, what is the purpose of this sport?</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>TRAVIS:  They've got these fargans. They're kind of like cows with humps, and they love melons. I think they're melons. So, four guys get into this big circle filled with fargans and they throw these melons back and forth. They use sticks with metal baskets at the end. Do you play monkey-in-the-middle on Denobula?</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>PHLOX:  I don't believe so.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>TRAVIS:  Anyway, after a while, the fargans start figuring out what's going on, and</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>TUCKER:  (interrupting) You got a minute, Doc?</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>PHLOX:  Are you not feeling well, Commander?</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>TUCKER:  No, I'm fine. I just, er, I need to talk to you for a minute.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>PHLOX:  By all means. What's on your mind?</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>TUCKER:  Actually, I was kind of hoping to talk to you alone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>PHLOX:  I think we're about done here. It would be best if you avoided fargans for a few days.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>TRAVIS:  Thanks, Doc. Commander.</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Travis leaves.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>TUCKER:  See you, Travis. Malcolm said this was a bad idea, but I, I think it's the right thing to do.</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>PHLOX:  What's that?</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>TUCKER:  Feezal, I mean, Mrs. Phlox, is a lovely woman, and she's very smart. She knows more about quantum optics than anyone I've ever met.</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>PHLOX:  She is remarkable.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>TUCKER:  Remarkable, yeah, she sure is.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>PHLOX:  Was there something else?</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>TUCKER:  Yeah, there is. You got to understand, I've been a perfect gentleman. Absolutely nothing's happened. She's trying to. She's, she's, er, making advances, if you know what I mean?</td></tr>

<tr id="L357"><td><a href="#L357">357</a></td><td>PHLOX:  Sexual advances?</td></tr>

<tr id="L358"><td><a href="#L358">358</a></td><td>TUCKER:  I'm afraid so.</td></tr>

