<tr id="L360"><td><a href="#L360">360</a></td><td>TUCKER:  No, no, no. Nothing like that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L361"><td><a href="#L361">361</a></td><td>PHLOX:  Oh, any man would be a fool to ignore the romantic overtures of a healthy Denobulan woman. Don't you find her attractive?</td></tr>

<tr id="L362"><td><a href="#L362">362</a></td><td>TUCKER:  Sure. I mean, no, she's your wife.</td></tr>

<tr id="L363"><td><a href="#L363">363</a></td><td>PHLOX:  What does that have to do with it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L364"><td><a href="#L364">364</a></td><td>TUCKER:  She's your wife?</td></tr>

<tr id="L365"><td><a href="#L365">365</a></td><td>PHLOX:  Oh, nonsense. Nonsense. You're too concerned with human morality. I thought you wanted to learn about new cultures. Isn't that why you joined Starfleet?</td></tr>

<tr id="L366"><td><a href="#L366">366</a></td><td>TUCKER:  Why, of course it is. But I was brought up believing you don't play around with another man's wife. I don't think I'm ever going to change my mind about that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L367"><td><a href="#L367">367</a></td><td>PHLOX:  As you wish. Your loss.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--T'Pol's quarters</td></tr>
<tr id="L368"><td><a href="#L368">368</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: T'Pol is packing her ornaments when the door chimes.</td></tr>

