<tr id="L379"><td><a href="#L379">379</a></td><td>T'POL:  You need to understand. I won't tell them how I got the disease.</td></tr>

<tr id="L380"><td><a href="#L380">380</a></td><td>ARCHER:  I'll go along with that. I promise. But you've got to understand, I'm not going to give you up without a fight.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Vulcan medical area</td></tr>
<tr id="L381"><td><a href="#L381">381</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Yuris, Oratt and Stromm are sitting at a long table, with Archer and T'Pol on chairs opposite.</td></tr>

<tr id="L382"><td><a href="#L382">382</a></td><td>STROMM:  The fact that she has Pa'nar Syndrome is not the reason she's being recalled.</td></tr>

<tr id="L383"><td><a href="#L383">383</a></td><td>ARCHER:  No. It has to do with how she got infected. A mind meld over a year ago.</td></tr>

<tr id="L384"><td><a href="#L384">384</a></td><td>STROMM:  When it took place is not pertinent.</td></tr>

<tr id="L385"><td><a href="#L385">385</a></td><td>ARCHER:  So what you're saying is that if a Vulcan, even an officer in the Science Directorate, engages in this exchange of thoughts and memories, they're condemned for it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L386"><td><a href="#L386">386</a></td><td>ORATT:  As you've been told, Captain, mind melds are practiced by a subculture. Vulcans who have elected to conduct themselves in an unacceptable manner.</td></tr>

<tr id="L387"><td><a href="#L387">387</a></td><td>T'POL:  They haven't elected to do anything. They're born with this ability.</td></tr>

<tr id="L388"><td><a href="#L388">388</a></td><td>STROMM:  Exactly. They're genetic aberrations who prey on people like you. People foolish enough to experiment with abhorrent behaviour.</td></tr>

<tr id="L389"><td><a href="#L389">389</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You humans are too volatile, too irrational, too narrow-minded. That's what I heard for years, from every Vulcan I met. But we don't hold a candle to you when it comes to narrow-minded. We got rid of bigotry nearly a century ago. We're not afraid of diversity. We don't persecute it, we embrace it. If you call yourselves enlightened, you have to accept people who are different than you are.</td></tr>

<tr id="L390"><td><a href="#L390">390</a></td><td>STROMM:  This is pointless. Our culture is governed by rules. We're not about to ignore them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L391"><td><a href="#L391">391</a></td><td>T'POL:  There are no rules telling you to oppress minorities.</td></tr>

<tr id="L392"><td><a href="#L392">392</a></td><td>STROMM:  You'd rather let them spread their infections. That's exactly why you're being recalled.</td></tr>

<tr id="L393"><td><a href="#L393">393</a></td><td>T'POL:  No, I'm being recalled because you're afraid of anything that doesn't conform to your idea of acceptable behaviour.</td></tr>

<tr id="L394"><td><a href="#L394">394</a></td><td>STROMM:  Unfortunately, you don't know what you're talking about. The decision's been made. We should end this inquiry.</td></tr>

<tr id="L395"><td><a href="#L395">395</a></td><td>YURIS:  She knows exactly what she's talking about.</td></tr>

<tr id="L396"><td><a href="#L396">396</a></td><td>ORATT:  Are you questioning our judgement?</td></tr>

<tr id="L397"><td><a href="#L397">397</a></td><td>YURIS:  There is nothing abhorrent about the way we lead our lives.</td></tr>

<tr id="L398"><td><a href="#L398">398</a></td><td>STROMM:  We?</td></tr>

<tr id="L399"><td><a href="#L399">399</a></td><td>YURIS:  There is no simple definition of intimacy. Those of us capable of mind-melds are no different than you are.</td></tr>

<tr id="L400"><td><a href="#L400">400</a></td><td>ORATT:  You realise that you are jeopardising your reputation, your career?</td></tr>

<tr id="L401"><td><a href="#L401">401</a></td><td>YURIS:  We share our thoughts differently. We shouldn't be punished for that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L402"><td><a href="#L402">402</a></td><td>ORATT:  The High Command will determine whether you should be punished. Both of you. (stands to leave)</td></tr>

<tr id="L403"><td><a href="#L403">403</a></td><td>YURIS:  She's not guilty of anything. She was violated.</td></tr>

<tr id="L404"><td><a href="#L404">404</a></td><td>T'POL:  You gave me your word.</td></tr>

<tr id="L405"><td><a href="#L405">405</a></td><td>YURIS:  The mind-meld was performed against her will.</td></tr>

<tr id="L406"><td><a href="#L406">406</a></td><td>ORATT:  Can you verify this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L407"><td><a href="#L407">407</a></td><td>T'POL:  Why? So you can perpetuate your double standard? Condemn the infected when they meld by choice and sympathise with them when they don't?</td></tr>

<tr id="L408"><td><a href="#L408">408</a></td><td>ORATT:  What do you know of this, Captain?</td></tr>

<tr id="L409"><td><a href="#L409">409</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Seems my Science Officer doesn't want to discuss it. That's good enough for me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L410"><td><a href="#L410">410</a></td><td>YURIS:  She told me herself. She made me promise to stay silent. I'm sorry. I had to tell them the truth. You should do the same.</td></tr>

<tr id="L411"><td><a href="#L411">411</a></td><td>T'POL:  I have nothing to say to them.</td></tr>

